What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Allantoin Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Allantoin Market

Allantoin market will grow at a rate of 6.25% for the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Increasing product demand for the manufacturing of various personal care products including shampoos, conditioners, mouthwash, and toothpaste is a vital factor driving the growth of allantoin market.

Allantoin is also called 5-ureidohydantoin or glyoxyldiureide, it is a crystalline oxidation product which is used to heal local wounds and infection. It is an odourless white powder produced by the oxidation of uric acid and are found in urine of many mammals except for human and primates and in botanical extracts of the comfrey plant. They are usually present in toothpaste, mouth, shampoo, lipsticks, lotion etc.

Rising awareness of healthy skin and hair among consumers is the vital factor escalating the market growth, also rising growth of cosmetics market, increasing growth in pharmaceutical sector, rising drug and medicine developments worldwide for rising diseases including Ebola and H1N1, increasing presence of major cosmetic manufacturing companies in the U.S. and rising use of allantoin in cosmetic and pharmaceutical applications are the major factors among others driving the allantoin market. Moreover, rising demand for the product in manufacturing cosmetic products due to its superior properties such as desquamation of dead skill cells, increasing the moisture content of skin and rising research and development activities in the market will further create new opportunities for the allantoin market in the forecast period of 2021- 2028.

However, rising regional raw material issues and lack of consumer awareness are the major factors among others acting as restraints, and will further challenge the growth of allantoin market in the forecast period mentioned above.

